      "content": "I understand the hassle, but I strongly advise against self-medicating with ibuprofen while on lithium, as NSAIDs can interact with the medication and affect your kidney function. While a week of hydration might help with mild side effects, if the symptoms don't improve, you risk serious issues. For your safety, try to find a low-cost clinic or telehealth option to get your lithium levels checked soon.",
